FAQs: Agent name goes in cell B1, the date goes in Call D1. F1 is the search string, automatically calculated based on the agent name and date. C3 automatically counts the number of tickets the agent has touched (you can just change the agent name to show the correct value)
column D in the table has the formula =IF(IFERROR(SEARCH($F$1,C5),0)=0,0,1) - it's easiest to work from the middle out to understand
SEARCH($F$1,C5) searches for the string in F1 in the cell C5 (this is the worknotes column. you will need to change this if you have more columns)

in case the string is not found, there will be an error, but if the string is found, it will return the position of the string. this is all wrapped in an IFERROR() function that will catch the error, and replace it with 0
the final step is the IF(), which checks if the value from the IFERROR is 0 or not. if the IFERROR is not 0, then it will display 1, otherwise, it will display 0
you can change these by modifying the last two arguments in the formula from 0,1 to 'false', 'true', or whatever other value you want
if you want to check the additional comments, then you can create a new column with the following: =IF(IFERROR(SEARCH($F$1,**additional comments cell**),0)=0,0,1)

then create a third column with the formula =IF(**column with worknotes result**+**column with additional comments result** > 0, 1, 0) - this will add the two results, and return 1 if the answer is greater than 0
